<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.156/228</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-10T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 319, March 24. Department unofficially informed that Ferrara has
                            prepared and submitted to other members of the commission, independent
                            report on Cuban Ports matter, showing various methods by which
                            settlement might be reached.</p>
                        <pb facs="0604" n="438" xml:id="pg_438"/>
                        <p>In view of time elapsed since date of decree, you may discreetly inquire
                            as to what progress has been made in this matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>